main event: A UFO sighting was reported in Ozone Park, New York on 4 September 1965, which was identified as a satellite echo.
interesting points: The sighting occurred at approximately 8:30 p.m. and involved two unidentified objects that appeared round and metallic., The first object crossed the sky in about 30 seconds, followed by a second object one minute later., The stated direction of the objects was north to south., There were no sounds heard from the objects during the observation., The report referenced was part of the Project Blue Book, a United States Air Force program investigating UFO sightings.
sighted object: two unidentified metallic objects in the sky
witness description: The witness observed the objects moving at a steady rate of speed and did not believe they were aircraft.
